-------------------------------------------------------------------------------\
SiteDiagramGUI                                                 By Casey Harford
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SiteDiagramGUI can be used to create a virtual world with buildings, sidewalks, 
roads, and many other objects(see full list below).

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------\
Requirements
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To run, you'll require the Java Runtime Environment, version 1.6 or greater, 
may work on old versions as well, but untested.

To compile, you'll require the Java Development Kit, version 1.6 or greater,
may work on old versions as well, but untested.

Both are available @  http://www.oracle.com

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------\
How to compile
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Navigate to the root of the project directory. Execute the following command:

  javac src/*.java -d bin/

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------\
How to use it
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Navigate to the bin directory, and excute the following command:

  java SiteDiagramGUI

You will be presented with a graph, and buttons along the top. The first set
of buttons contain objects that can be built, then you can select a color,
and a size for the object using the next set of buttons.

Multiple objects can be built, here are the list of available objects:
- tree
- grass
- building
- sidewalk
- road
- house

Sizes include
- Small(Default)
- Medium
- Large

To select a color, click the color button, which will dislplay a dialog with
a selection of colors to choose from. Once you've selected a color, click Done.

